title.narrative: Technical service provision for microfinance, banking, equity and programming in the horticulture, leather and cotton industries including monitoring and evaluation

description.narrative: This activity (Technical service provision for microfinance, banking, equity and programming in the horticulture, leather and cotton industries including monitoring and evaluation) is a component of Private Enterprise Programme Ethiopia reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Procurement of Services' and a budget of £44,096,763. This component benefits Ethiopia, and works in the following sector(s): Formal sector financial intermediaries, Agricultural policy and administrative management, Agricultural development, Livestock, Agricultural services, Industrial development, Research/scientific institutions. , with the following implementing partners: Crown Agents Limited, DAI Europe. The start date is 02-04-2013 and the end date is 31-12-2020.
